{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.7",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
    "chapterNumber": 7,
    "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 7",
    "summary": "Source text for Song of Solomon 7 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.7.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 7:1",
      "text": "How graceful are your feet in sandals, O queenly maiden! Your rounded thighs are like jewels, the work of a master hand.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.7.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 7:2",
      "text": "Your navel is a rounded bowl that never lacks mixed wine. Your belly is a heap of wheat, encircled with lilies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.7.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 7:3",
      "text": "Your two breasts are like two fawns, twins of a gazelle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.7.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 7:4",
      "text": "Your neck is like an ivory tower. Your eyes are pools in Heshbon, by the gate of Bath-rabbim. Your nose is like a tower of Lebanon, overlooking Damascus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.7.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 7:5",
      "text": "Your head crowns you like Carmel, and your flowing locks are like purple; a king is held captive in the tresses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.7.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 7:6",
      "text": "How fair and pleasant you are, O loved one, delectable maiden!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.7.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 7:7",
      "text": "You are stately as a palm tree, and your breasts are like its clusters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.7.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 7:8",
      "text": "I say I will climb the palm tree and lay hold of its branches. Oh, may your breasts be like clusters of the vine, and the scent of your breath like apples,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.7.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 7:9",
      "text": "and your kisses like the best wine that goes down smoothly, gliding over lips and teeth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.7.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 7:10",
      "text": "I am my beloved's, and his desire is for me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.7.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 7:11",
      "text": "Come, my beloved, let us go forth into the fields, and lodge in the villages;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.7.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 7:12",
      "text": "let us go out early to the vineyards, and see whether the vines have budded, whether the grape blossoms have opened and the pomegranates are in bloom. There I will give you my love.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.7.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 7:13",
      "text": "The mandrakes give forth fragrance, and over our doors are all choice fruits, new as well as old, which I have laid up for you, O my beloved.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
